==Customization==
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#000080|Setting your appearance}}<br>Before you get started, you'll need to set the appearance of your character. Please use the open interface to set your appearance.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#000080|Past Experience}}<br>Before you get started, please use the open interface to select your experience with Old School RuneScape.}}
** {{topt|I'm brand new! This is my first time here.}}
** {{topt|I've played in the past, but not recently.}}
** {{topt|I'm an experienced player.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#000080|Getting started}}<br>When you're ready to get started, click on the Gielinor Guide. He is indicated by a flashing yellow arrow.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Gielinor Guide==
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' Greetings! I see you are a new arrival to the world of Gielinor. My job is to welcome all new visitors. So welcome!
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' You have already learned the first thing needed to succeed in this world: talking to other people!
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' You will find many inhabitants of this world have useful things to say to you. By [clicking/tapping] on them you can talk to them.
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' Now then, let's start by looking at your settings menu.
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#000080|Settings menu}}<br>Please [click/tap] on the flashing spanner icon found on the bottom right of your screen. This will display your settings menu.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to leave the building before finishing the beginning tutorial===
* {{tbox|You need to talk to the Gielinor Guide before you are allowed to proceed through this door.}}

===After opening settings menu===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#000080|Settings menu}}<br>On the side panel, you can now see a variety of game settings. You can also [click/tap] the all settings button to see all available settings. Talk to the Gielinor Guide to continue.}}
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' Looks like you're making good progress! The menu you've just opened is one of many. You'll learn about the rest as you progress through the tutorial.
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' Anyway, I'd say it's time for you to go and meet your first instructor!
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>It's time to meet your first instructor. To continue, all you need to do is [click/tap] on the door. It's indicated by a flashing yellow arrow. Remember, you can [swipe across the screen/use your arrow keys] to rotate the camera.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Gielinor Guide again===
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' Welcome back. You have already learnt the first thing needed to succeed in this world: talking to other people!
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' You will find many inhabitants of this world have useful things to say to you. By [clicking/tapping] on them, you can talk to them.
* '''Gielinor Guide:''' To continue the tutorial go through that door over there and speak to your first instructor!
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>It's time to meet your first instructor. To continue, all you need to do is [click/tap] on the door. It's indicated by a flashing yellow arrow. Remember, you can [swipe across the screen/use your arrow keys] to rotate the camera.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Survival Expert==
===Attempting to chop down a tree before talking to the Survival Expert===
* {{tbox|You cannot cut down this tree yet. You must progress further in the tutorial.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to fish for shrimp before talking to the Survival Expert===
* {{tbox|You cannot fish here yet. You must progress further in the tutorial.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Survival Expert===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Hello there, newcomer. My name is Brynna. My job is to teach you about the skills you can use to survive in this world.
* '''Survival Expert:''' The first skill we're going to look at is Fishing. There's some shrimp in this pond here. Let's try and catch some.
* {{tact|receives=a small fishing net}}
* {{tbox|pic=Small fishing net detail.png|The survival expert gives you a {{Colour|#000080|small fishing net}}.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|You've been given an item}}<br>To view the item you've been given, you'll need to open your inventory. To do so, [click/tap] on the flashing backpack icon to the right hand side of your screen.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to leave through the gate before finishing the survival tutorial===
* {{tbox|You need to talk to the Survival Guide and complete her tasks before you are allowed to proceed through this gate.}}

===After opening inventory===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Inventory}}<br>This is your inventory. You can view all of your items here, including the net you've just been given. Let's use it to catch some shrimp.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Before fishing===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Hello again. First up, we're going to do some fishing. There's some shrimp in this pond here. Let's try and catch some.
* {{tact|end}}

===After clicking on a fishing spot===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to catch some shrimp. Sit back for a moment while [he does/she does/they do] all the hard work.}}
* {{tbox|pic=Raw shrimps detail.png|You manage to catch some shrimp.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|You've gained some experience}}<br>[Click/Tap] on the flashing bar graph icon near the inventory button to see your skills menu.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Before opening skills menu===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Hello again. You should take a look at that menu before we continue.
* {{tact|end}}

===After opening skills menu===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Skills and Experience}}<br> On this menu you can view your skills. Your skills can be leveled up by earning experience. As you level up your skills, you will earn new unlocks. Speak to the survival expert to continue.
}}
* {{tact|opens=Skills}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After fishing===
* '''Player:''' I've managed to catch some shrimp.
* '''Survival Expert:''' Excellent work. Next you'll want to cook those shrimp. To do that, you'll need a fire. This brings us on to the Woodcutting and Firemaking skills.
* {{tbox|pic=bronze axe detail.png|pic2=tinderbox detail.png|The survival expert gives you a {{Colour|#000080|bronze axe}} and a {{Colour|#000080|tinderbox}}.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Woodcutting}}<br>It's time to cook your shrimp. However, you require a fire to do that which means you need some logs. You can cut down trees using your Woodcutting skill, all you need is an axe. Give it a go by clicking on one of the trees in the area.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Before cutting a tree===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Next up you need to make a fire. First, you'll need to cut down a tree to get some logs.
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to equip an item before learning how to equip items===
* {{tbox|You'll be told how to equip items later.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After clicking on a tree===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to cut down the tree. Sit back for a moment while [he/she] does all the hard work.}}
* {{tbox|pic=logs detail.png|You manage to cut some logs.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Firemaking}}<br>Now that you have some logs, it's time to light a fire. First, [click/tap] on the tinderbox in your inventory. Then, with the tinderbox highlighted, [click/tap] on the logs to use the tinderbox on them.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Before lighting a fire===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Now that you have some shrimp, you're going to want to cook them. To do that, you'll need a fire.
* {{tact|end}}

===After using tinderbox on logs===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to light a fire. This should only take a few seconds.}}
* {{tcond|If playing on desktop:}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Cooking}}<br>Now it's time to get cooking. To do so, [click/tap] on the shrimp in your inventory. Then, with the shrimp highlighted, [click/tap] on a fire to cook them. If you look at the top left of the screen, you'll see the instructions that you're giving to your character.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If playing on mobile:}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Cooking}}<br>Now it's time to get cooking. To do so, [click/tap] on the shrimp in your inventory. Then, with the shrimp highlighted, [click/tap] on a fire to cook them.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Before cooking the shrimp===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Now that you have some shrimp, you're going to want to cook them. All you need to do is use them on a fire.
* {{tact|end}}

===After using shrimp on fire===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to cook some shrimp. This will only take a few seconds.}}
* {{tcond|If successfully cooked:}}
** {{tbox|pic=shrimps detail.png|You manage to cook some shrimp.}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Well done, you've just cooked your first meal! Speak to the survival expert if you want a recap, otherwise you can move on. [Click/Tap] on the gate shown and follow the path. Remember, you can [swipe across the screen/use your arrow keys] to rotate the camera.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the shrimp burned:}}
** {{tbox|pic=burnt shrimp detail.png|You accidently{{sic}} burn the shrimp.}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Oh no, you've just burnt your meal! Speak to the survival expert if you want a recap, otherwise you can move on. [Click/Tap] on the gate shown and follow the path. Remember, you can [swipe across the screen/use your arrow keys] to rotate the camera.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Cooking more shrimp===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to cook some shrimp. This will only take a few seconds.}}
* {{tcond|If the player successfully cooks the shrimp:}}
** {{tbox|You manage to cook some shrimp.}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Well done, you've just cooked another meal! Speak to the survival expert if you want a recap, otherwise you can move on. [Click/Tap] on the gate shown and follow the path. Remember, you can [swipe across the screen]/[use your arrow keys] to rotate the camera.}}
* {{tcond|If the shrimp burned:}}
** {{tact|above}}

===Speaking to the Survival Expert again===
* '''Survival Expert:''' Hello again. Is there something you'd like to hear more about?
* {{topt|Tell me about my skills again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about my skills again.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Every skill is listed in the skills menu. Here you can see what your current levels are and how much experience you have.
** '''Survival Expert:''' As you move your mouse over the various skills the small tooltip will show you the exact amount of experience you have and how much is needed to get to the next level.
** '''Survival Expert:''' You can also [click/tap] on a skill to open up the relevant skillguide. In the skillguide, you can see all of the unlocks available in that skill.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Is there anything else you'd like to hear more about?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Tell me about Woodcutting again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about Woodcutting again.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Woodcutting, eh? Don't worry, newcomer, it's really very easy. Simply equip your axe and [click/tap] on a nearby tree to chop away.
** '''Survival Expert:''' As you explore the mainland you will discover many different kinds of trees that will require different Woodcutting levels to chop down.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Logs are not only useful for making fires. Many archers use the skill known as Fletching to craft their own bows and arrows from trees.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Is there anything else you'd like to hear more about?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Tell me about Firemaking again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about Firemaking again.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Certainly, newcomer. When you have logs simply use your tinderbox on them. If successful, you will start a fire.
** '''Survival Expert:''' You can also set fire to logs you find lying on the floor already, and some other things can also be set alight...
** '''Survival Expert:''' A tinderbox is always a useful item to keep around!
** '''Survival Expert:''' Is there anything else you'd like to hear more about?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Tell me about Fishing again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about Fishing again.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Ah, yes. Fishing! Fishing is undoubtedly one of the more popular hobbies here in Gielinor!
** '''Survival Expert:''' Whenever you see sparkling waters, you can be sure there's probably some good fishing to be had there!
** '''Survival Expert:''' Not only are fish absolutely delicious when cooked, they will also heal lost health.
** '''Survival Expert:''' I would recommend everybody has a go at Fishing at least once in their lives!
** '''Survival Expert:''' Is there anything else you'd like to hear more about?
** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|Tell me about Cooking again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about Cooking again.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Yes, the most basic of survival techniques. Most simple foods can be used on a fire to cook them. If you're feeling a bit fancier, you can also use a range to cook the food instead.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Eating cooked food will restore lost health. The harder something is to cook, the more it will heal you.
** '''Survival Expert:''' Is there anything else you'd like to hear more about?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Nothing thanks.}}
** '''Player:''' Nothing thanks.
** {{tact|end}}

===After opening the gate===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Follow the path to find until you get to the door with the yellow arrow above it. [Click/Tap] on the door to open it. Remember that you can also move around by [clicking]/[tapping] on the minimap in the top right.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to chop down a tree===
* {{tcond|Normal tree:}}
**  {{tbox|Perhaps you've done enough woodcutting now.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|Oak tree:}}
**  {{tbox|You won't be able to chop oak trees until you have a Woodcutting level of 15. You'll advance to higher Woodcutting levels by chopping down normal trees. At higher Woodcutting levels you will find even more trees you can cut.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Attemping to pick up an item without sufficient inventory space===
* {{tcond|If playing on desktop:}}
** {{tbox|You don't have enough inventory space to hold that item.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If plying on mobile:}}
** {{tbox|([Current time in UTC]) You don't have enough inventory space to hold that item.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to perform an action outside of the character's range===
* {{tcond|If playing on desktop:}}
** {{tbox|I can't reach that!}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If playing on mobile:}}
** {{tbox|([Current time in UTC]) I can't reach that!}}
** {{tact|end}}

==Master Chef==
===Opening the Master Chef's door===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Cooking}}<br>Talk to learn the more advanced aspects of Cooking such as combining ingredients!}}

===Attempting to use the range without bread dough===
* {{tbox|You haven't got anything suitable for cooking! The master chef can help you out with that.}}

===Attempting to leave through the exit before finishing the cooking tutorial===
* {{tbox|You need to finish the Master Chef's tasks first.}}

===Talking to the Master Chef===
* '''Master Chef:''' Ah! Welcome, newcomer. I am the Master Chef, Lev. It is here that I will teach you how to cook food truly fit for a king.
* '''Player:''' I already know how to cook. Brynna taught me just now.
* '''Master Chef:''' Hahahahahaha! You call THAT cooking? Some shrimp on an open log fire? Oh, no, no, no. I am going to teach you the fine art of cooking bread.
* {{tact|receives=a pot of flour and a bucket of water}}
* {{tbox|pic=Pot of flour detail.png|pic2=Bucket of water detail.png|The master chef gives you some {{Colour|#000080|flour}} and some {{Colour|#000080|water}}.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Making dough}}<br>This is the base for many meals. To make dough you must mix flour with water. To do so, [click/tap] on the flour in your inventory. Then, with the flour highlighted, [click/tap] on the water to combine them into dough.}}

===Talking to the Master Chef before cooking the dough===
* '''Master Chef:''' Time for you to learn the fine art of cooking bread.
* {{tcond|If the player has neither flour nor water:}}
** {{tact|receives=a pot of flour and a bucket of water}}
** {{tbox|pic=Pot of flour detail.png|pic2=Bucket of water detail.png|The master chef gives you some {{Colour|#000080|flour}} and some {{Colour|#000080|water}}.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player only has flour:}}
** {{Tact|receives=bucket of water}}
* {{tbox|pic=bucket of water detail.png|The master chef gives you some {{Colour|#000080|water}}.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player only has water:}}
** {{tact|receives=a pot of flour}}
** {{tbox|pic=pot of flour detail.png|The master chef gives you some {{Colour|#000080|flour}}.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Making the dough===
* {{tbox|pic=Bread dough detail.png|You make some dough.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Cooking dough}}<br>Now you have made the dough, you can bake it into some bread. To do so, just [click/tap] on the indicated range.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Cooking the dough===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to bake some bread. This will take a few seconds.}}
* {{tbox|pic=bread detail.png|You manage to bake some bread.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Well done! You've baked your first loaf of bread. As you gain experience in Cooking, you will be able to make other things like pies and cakes. You can now use the next door to move on. If you need a recap on anything, talk to the master chef.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Cooking more dough===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to bake some bread. This will take a few seconds.}}
* {{tcond|If the player is successful:}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{tcond|If the player burns the bread:}}
** {{tbox|pic=burnt bread detail.png|You accidently burn the bread.}}
** {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Well done!{{sic}} You've baked your first loaf of bread. As you gain experience in Cooking, you will be able to make other things like pies and cakes. You can now use the next door to move on. If you need a recap on anything, talk to the master chef.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Master Chef again===
* '''Master Chef:''' Do you need something?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Tell me about making dough again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about making dough again.
** '''Master Chef:''' It's quite simple. Just use a pot of flour on a bucket of water, or vice versa, and you'll make dough. You can fill a bucket with water at any sink.
** '''Master Chef:''' Do you need anything else?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Tell me about range cooking again.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about range cooking again.
** '''Master Chef:''' The range is the only place you can cook a lot of the more complex foods in Gielinor. To cook on a range, all you need to do is [click/tap] on it. You'll need to make sure you have the required items in your inventory though.
** '''Master Chef:''' Do you need anything else?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Nothing thanks.}}
** '''Player:''' Nothing thanks.
** {{tact|end}}

===Opening the exit door===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Fancy a run?}}<br>When navigating the world, you can either run or walk. Running is faster but you can't run for long as you'll soon run out of energy. You can use the flashing orb next to the minimap to toggle running. Why not try it as you head to the next section?}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After toggling the run button===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>Follow the path to the next guide. When you get there, [click/tap] on the door to pass through it. Remember, you can [use your arrow keys/swipe across the screen] to rotate the camera.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Quest Guide==
===Opening the Quest Guide's door===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Quests}}<br>It's time to learn about quests! Just talk to the Quest Guide to get started.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening to go down the ladder before talking to the Quest Guide===
* '''Quest Guide:''' I don't think you're ready to go down there yet.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Quest Guide===
* '''Quest Guide:''' Ah. Welcome, adventurer. I'm here to tell you all about quests. Let's start by opening your quest list.
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Quest journal}}<br>[Click]/[tap] on the flashing icon to the left of your inventory.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Quest Guide before opening your quest journal===
* '''Quest Guide:''' Have you not opened that menu yet?
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening the quest journal===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Quest journal}}<br>This is your quest journal. It lists every quest in the game. Talk to the quest guide again for an explanation on how it works.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Quest Guide after viewing the quest journal===
* '''Quest Guide:''' Now that you have the quest list open, you can see all the quests within it. Opening a quest's journal will provide you with more information on it.
* '''Quest Guide:''' If you haven't started the quest, it will tell you where to begin and what requirements you need. If the quest is in progress, it will remind you what to do next.
* '''Quest Guide:''' It's very easy to find quest start points. Just look out for the quest icon on your minimap. You should see one marking this house.
* {{tbox|pic=Quests.png|The minimap in the top right corner of the screen has various icons to show different points of interest. Look for the icon to the left to find quest start points.}}
* '''Quest Guide:''' The quests themselves can vary greatly from collecting beads to hunting down dragons. Completing quests will reward you with all sorts of things, such as new areas and better weapons!
* '''Quest Guide:''' There's not a lot more I can tell you about questing. You have to experience the thrill of it yourself to fully understand. Let me know if you want a recap, otherwise you can move on.
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Moving on}}<br>It's time to enter some caves. [Click/Tap] on the ladder to go down to the next area.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Quest Guide again===
* '''Quest Guide:''' Would you like to hear about quests again?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Yes!}}
** '''Player:''' Yes!
** '''Quest Guide:''' Within your quest list, you'll unsurprisingly find a list of quests. Opening a quest's journal will provide you with more information on it.
** '''Quest Guide:''' If you haven't started the quest, it will tell you where to begin and what requirements you need. If the quest is in progress, it will remind you what to do next.
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Nope, I'm ready to move on!}}
** '''Player:''' Nope, I'm ready to move on!
** '''Quest Guide:''' Okay then.
** {{tact|end}}

==Mining Instructor==
===After entering the caves===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Mining and Smithing}}<br>Next let's get you a weapon, or more to the point, you can make your first weapon yourself. Don't panic, the mining instructor will help you. Talk to him and he'll tell you all about it.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to leave through the exit before finishing the Mining and Smithing tutorial===
* {{tbox|You need to finish with Mining and Smithing first.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to mine without a pickaxe===
* {{tbox|You are not ready to mine yet. Please follow the tutorial and you'll be mining in no time.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to use an anvil before learning how to use it===
* {{tbox|This is an anvil used for smithing. You'll learn how to use it soon.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to use the furnace before learning how to use it===
* {{tbox|This is a furnace for smelting metal. You'll learn how to use it soon.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Mining Instructor===
* '''Mining Instructor:''' Hi there. You must be new around here. So what do I call you? 'Newcomer' seems so impersonal, and if we're going to be working together, I'd rather call you by name.
* '''Player:''' You can call me [player name].
* '''Mining Instructor:''' Ok then, [player name]. My name is Dezzick and I'm a miner by trade. Let's teach you how to mine.
* '''Mining Instructor:''' Mining is very simple, all you need is a pickaxe. The rocks around here contain tin and copper. Why don't you get started by mining some?
* {{tact|receives=a bronze pickaxe}}
* {{tbox|pic=Bronze pickaxe detail.png|The mining instructor gives you a {{Colour|#000080|bronze pickaxe}}.}} 
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Mining}}<br>It's quite simple really. To mine a rock, all you need to do is [click/tap] on it. First up, try mining some tin.}}

===Mining a rock===
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Please Wait}}<br>Your character is now attempting to mine the rock. This should only take a few seconds.}}
* {{tbox|You manage to mine some [tin/copper].}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Mining}}<br>Now that you have some [tin/copper] ore, you just need some [copper/tin] To mine a rock, all you need to do is [click/tap] on it.}}

===Before obtaining both ores===
* '''Mining Instructor:''' The rocks around here contain tin and copper. You should try mining some.
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to mine ore with a full inventory===
* {{tbox|You don't have enough room in your inventory to hold the ore. You'll need to drop something. To do so, [tap and hold/right-click on] an item you don't want and select drop. Once you've done that, try mining the rock again.}}

===After obtaining both ores===
* '''Mining Instructor:''' Now that you have some ore, you should smelt it into a bronze bar. You can use the furnace over there to do so.
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Smelting}}<br>You now have some tin ore and some copper ore. You can smelt these into a bronze bar. To do so, just [click/tap] on the indicated furnace. Try it now.}}

===Smelting bronze===
* {{tbox|You smelt the copper and tin together in the furnace.}}
* {{tbox|You retrieve a bar of bronze.}}
* {{tbox|{{Colour|#0000ff|Smithing}}<br>You've made a bronze bar! Speak to the mining instructor and he'll show you how to make it into a weapon.}}

===Attempting to use an anvil before receiving a hammer===
* {{tbox|You need a hammer to work the metal with. Talk to the mining instructor to get one.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Mining Instructor after smelting a bronze bar===
* '''Player:''' I have a bronze bar. What now?
* '''Mining Instructor:''' Now that you've got a bar, you can smith it into a weapon. To smith something, you need a hammer and an anvil. There's some anvils just here that you can use. See if you can make a bronze dagger.
